*The WeRateDogs twitter data is gathered,assesed and cleaned for analysis.*

*The clean master data contains the consolidated data from the twitter archive,image prediction and tweet count data sets with columns prediction,retweet count,favorites count,confidence percentage,image urls etc.*

*The features that are inetersted in this analysis are the retweet count,favorites count,rating, dog type, prediction and confidence percentage.*

*The most predicted breeds were Golden retriever,Labrador,Pembroke,chihuahua,pug.But when taken the mean favorites count and retweet count ,none of these breeds were shown.*

*But the mean favorites and retweet count on breed prediction showed some common breeds,except for a few.
Also the breeds with high rating like clumber  ,had low favorites and retweet count while Labrador,golden retriever,saluki were given low rating but had most favorites and retweet count.*

*In terms of dog type,floofer has the highest mean rating followed by puppo,doggo and pupper.
Most of the breeds  predicted are under the dog type pupper,followed by doggo and puppo,Floofer has only 2 breeds predicted.*

*Lets look into some visualisations.I obsereved that the most favorite breeds were retweeted the most,in other way,favorites count and retweet count are in a linear relation.*

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import requests
import json
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline
import seaborn as sb

#donut chart for dog type %.
counts=df_twitter_master['dog_type'].value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False).head(4)
plt.pie(counts,labels=counts.index, wedgeprops={'width':0.4},startangle=90,counterclock=False,autopct='%.2f')
plt.axis('square')
plt.title('Dog Types');
*68% of the dogs are under the dog type pupper,followed by 21% doggo,7% puppo.*

#scatter plot for retweet count vs favorites count for dog type
dog_markers=[['doggo','s'],['puppo','p'],['pupper','*'],['flooper','h'],['doggo, floofer','1'],['doggo, pupper','2'],['doggo, puppo','3']]
for dog,markers in dog_markers:
    df_dog=df_twitter_master[df_twitter_master['dog_type']==dog]
    plt.scatter(data=df_dog,x='retweet_count',y='favorites_count',marker=markers)
    plt.xscale('log')
    plt.yscale('log')
    plt.xlabel('Retweet Count')
    plt.ylabel('Favorites Count')
    plt.title('Retweet vs Favorites of dog types ')
    plt.legend(['doggo','puppo','pupper','flooper','doggo, pupper','doggo, floofer','doggo, puppo'])
*From the above plot,retweet count increases with favourites count.We can conclude that favourite dog types are retweeted and retweeted dog types are favourites ones mostly.
The plot shows more green stars indicating high pupper type,followed by doggo in blue square,puppo in orange hexagon and floofer is hardly seen on the plot*

#pie chart for top 10 predicted dog breeds.
breeds = df_twitter_master.query('breed_predicted == True')
no_breeds = df_twitter_master.query('breed_predicted == False')
counts=breeds['prediction'].value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
plt.pie(counts,labels=counts.index,startangle=90,counterclock=False,autopct='%.2f')
plt.axis('square')
plt.title('Top 10 Predicted Dog breeds')
*From the above plot,which shows the top 10 prediction dog breeds, top prediction is 21.6% predicted Golden retriver and next is labrador retirver.*
*As the visualisations are from a clean data,the predictions can be considered accurate.*
